and the invariant interval, so the time-dilation factors drop out from first principles.<br></span>
<h1 data-start="142" data-end="161">Setup (as before)</h1>
<ul data-start="163" data-end="1070"><li data-start="163" data-end="325"><span><strong data-start="165" data-end="175">Frames</strong>:<br data-start="176" data-end="179">
<strong data-start="181" data-end="186">K</strong> with coordinates <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>t</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>; <strong data-start="216" data-end="221">k</strong> with <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.  Relative speed <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> along <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br data-start="278" data-end="281">
<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>β</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>c</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>γ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>β</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="327" data-end="473"><span><strong data-start="329" data-end="339">Clocks</strong>:<br data-start="340" data-end="343">
A,H at rest in <strong data-start="360" data-end="365">K</strong> at <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>H</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br data-start="389" data-end="392">
B,N at rest in <strong data-start="409" data-end="414">k</strong> at <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mi>B</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mi>N</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> (negative so A can meet N later).<br></span></li>
<li data-start="475" data-end="542"><span><strong data-start="477" data-end="493">Origin event</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>: A meets B at <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="544" data-end="779"><span><strong data-start="546" data-end="574">Lorentz transform (1+1D)</strong>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>β</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>γ</mi></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>γ</mi></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo separator="true">,</mo><mspace width="2em"></mspace><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>x</mi></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span></li>
<li data-start="781" data-end="1070"><span><strong data-start="783" data-end="805">Invariant interval</strong> (signature <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo>+</mo><mtext> </mtext><mo>−</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>):<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msup><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msup><mi>τ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mtext>(for&nbsp;timelike&nbsp;separation).</mtext></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>A clock’s <strong data-start="953" data-end="968">proper time</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>τ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> between two events on its own worldline is what that clock reads between those events.<br></span></li></ul>
<hr data-start="1072" data-end="1075">
<h1 data-start="1077" data-end="1103">Event <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>: H meets B</h1>
<h3 data-start="1105" data-end="1120">Coordinates</h3>
<ul data-start="1121" data-end="1438"><li data-start="1121" data-end="1156"><span>H is at rest in <strong data-start="1139" data-end="1144">K</strong>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="1157" data-end="1230"><span>B is at rest in <strong data-start="1175" data-end="1180">k</strong>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>. In <strong data-start="1195" data-end="1200">K</strong> this worldline is <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="1231" data-end="1438"><span>Intersection in <strong data-start="1249" data-end="1254">K</strong>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>. So<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><msub><mi>X</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mtext>in&nbsp;</mtext><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span></li></ul>
<span>Transform to <strong data-start="1453" data-end="1458">k</strong>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>L</mi></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>γ</mi><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi><mi>L</mi><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>γ</mi><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>β</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mn>0</mn></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>so <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and, as expected, <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> because this is on B’s rest worldline.<br></span>
<h3 data-start="1796" data-end="1838">Proper time viewpoint (B’s wristwatch)</h3>
<span>Proper time on B between <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> equals the primed coordinate time difference because B is at rest in <strong data-start="1953" data-end="1958">k</strong>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo>→</mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>Compute the same <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>τ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> from <strong data-start="2039" data-end="2044">K</strong> using the invariant interval:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msubsup><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>−</mo><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>−</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>v</mi><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>β</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow><msup><mi>γ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>so <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>γ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.  Hence<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mtable width="100%"><mtr><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mrow><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>γ</mi></mfrac><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mo>⟺</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mtext> </mtext><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></mtd><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mtext>(1)</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<hr data-start="2331" data-end="2334">
<h1 data-start="2336" data-end="2362">Event <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>: A meets N</h1>
<h3 data-start="2364" data-end="2379">Coordinates</h3>
<ul data-start="2380" data-end="2590"><li data-start="2380" data-end="2415"><span>A is at rest in <strong data-start="2398" data-end="2403">K</strong>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="2416" data-end="2509"><span>N is at rest in <strong data-start="2434" data-end="2439">k</strong>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.  In <strong data-start="2457" data-end="2462">K</strong>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span></li>
<li data-start="2510" data-end="2590"><span>Intersection with A’s worldline <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br></span></li></ul>
<span>Coordinates of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><msubsup><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center" columnspacing="1em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mrow><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mtext>in&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>

<span>so <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> as expected (it lies on A’s rest worldline).<br></span>
<h3 data-start="3112" data-end="3154">Proper time viewpoint (A’s wristwatch)</h3>
<span>Proper time on A between <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> equals the unprimed coordinate time difference because A is at rest in <strong data-start="3271" data-end="3276">K</strong>:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo>→</mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>Compute the same <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><mi>τ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> from <strong data-start="3356" data-end="3361">k</strong> using the invariant interval:<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msubsup><mi>τ</mi><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal">′</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>−</mo><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal">′</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal">′</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>−</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>L</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal">′</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>β</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo mathvariant="normal">′</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow><msup><mi>γ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<span>so <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>γ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>. Hence<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mtable width="100%"><mtr><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mrow><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mi>γ</mi></mfrac><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mo>⟺</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mtext> </mtext><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow></mtd><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mtext>(2)</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span></span></span>
<hr data-start="3651" data-end="3654">
<h1 data-start="3656" data-end="3706">The two “rate ratios,” now as proper-time ratios</h1>
<ul data-start="3708" data-end="4185"><li data-start="3708" data-end="3973"><span>Along B’s worldline (<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>):<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mtable width="100%"><mtr><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mrow><mfrac><mtext>rate&nbsp;of&nbsp;A</mtext><mtext>rate&nbsp;of&nbsp;B</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mtext>A’s&nbsp;elapsed&nbsp;time&nbsp;between&nbsp;the&nbsp;same&nbsp;endpoints&nbsp;in&nbsp;</mtext><mi>K</mi></mrow><mtext>B’s&nbsp;proper&nbsp;time&nbsp;between&nbsp;those&nbsp;endpoints</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>a</mi></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1.</mn></mrow></mtd><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mtext>(3)</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span></span></span></li>
<li data-start="3974" data-end="4185"><span>Along A’s worldline (<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>):<br></span>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mtable width="100%"><mtr><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mrow><mfrac><mtext>rate&nbsp;of&nbsp;A</mtext><mtext>rate&nbsp;of&nbsp;B</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>A’s&nbsp;proper&nbsp;time</mtext><mtext>B/N’s&nbsp;elapsed&nbsp;(primed)&nbsp;time</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>γ</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1.</mn></mrow></mtd><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mtext>(4)</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span></span></span></li></ul>
<span>So equations (1)–(4) follow directly from:<br></span>
<ol data-start="4230" data-end="4397"><li data-start="4230" data-end="4329"><span>picking the appropriate <strong data-start="4257" data-end="4270">worldline</strong> (which fixes whose elapsed time equals proper time), and<br></span></li>
<li data-start="4330" data-end="4397"><span>applying the <strong data-start="4346" data-end="4368">invariant interval</strong> between the same two events.<br></span></li></ol>
<hr data-start="4399" data-end="4402">
<h2 data-start="4404" data-end="4443">Why the “flip” isn’t a contradiction</h2>
<span>Both results compare <strong data-start="4466" data-end="4495">different pairs of events</strong> anchored to <strong data-start="4508" data-end="4533">different rest clocks</strong>. Proper time is path-dependent: B’s wristwatch between <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> is not the same physical path as A’s wristwatch between <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>. The invariant interval guarantees internal consistency; the apparent reversal comes from switching which worldline (and thus which simultaneity convention) defines the interval.<br></span>

flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light markdown-new-styling"><span>That’s an <em data-start="10" data-end="21">excellent</em> B.”<br></span>
<span>But there’s a subtle distinction worth unpacking carefully, because this is <strong data-start="298" data-end="309">exactly</strong> the point where Herbert Dingle’s objection — and Einstein’s original formulation — part ways conceptually. Let’s go step by step.<br></span>
<hr data-start="441" data-end="444">
<h2 data-start="446" data-end="498">1️⃣ “Along B’s worldline” — the geometric meaning</h2>
<span>When we say:<br></span>
<blockquote data-start="513" data-end="649">
<span>“Along B’s worldline (from <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> to <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>) the proper time elapsed is <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>, and A’s corresponding coordinate time is <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.”<br></span>
</blockquote>
<span>we’re describing an <strong data-start="671" data-end="699">objective geometric fact</strong> in spacetime:<br></span>
<ul data-start="715" data-end="996"><li data-start="715" data-end="778"><span>The worldline is the actual path B takes through spacetime.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="779" data-end="896"><span>The <strong data-start="785" data-end="800">proper time</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><msqrt><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></msqrt><mtext> </mtext><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> is the length of that path in Minkowski geometry.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="897" data-end="996"><span>It’s invariant — every observer agrees on the <em data-start="945" data-end="952">value</em> of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> between those two events.<br></span></li></ul>
<span>So “along B’s worldline” literally means “as measured by a clock physically carried by B,” and that’s not a matter of perspective or convention. It’s what B’s wristwatch reads.<br></span>
<span>Thus it is fair to say:<br></span>
<blockquote data-start="1200" data-end="1282">
<span>“In B’s own experience between <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>, a time <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msubsup></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> has passed.”<br></span>
</blockquote>
<span>because “B’s experience” = “B’s proper time.”<br></span>
<hr data-start="1331" data-end="1334">
<h2 data-start="1336" data-end="1379">2️⃣ “According to B” — the frame meaning</h2>
<span>When we say:<br></span>
<blockquote data-start="1394" data-end="1434">
<span>“According to B, A’s clock runs slow,”<br></span>
</blockquote>
<span>we’re shifting to a <strong data-start="1456" data-end="1471">frame-based</strong> statement.<br data-start="1482" data-end="1485">
Now we’re talking about all of spacetime from B’s <em data-start="1535" data-end="1561">inertial reference frame</em>, not just B’s personal worldline.<br></span>
<span>That involves:<br></span>
<ul data-start="1612" data-end="1836"><li data-start="1612" data-end="1696"><span>assigning simultaneity surfaces (“events that are simultaneous according to B”),<br></span></li>
<li data-start="1697" data-end="1781"><span>measuring A’s <em data-start="1713" data-end="1740">coordinate time intervals</em> between those simultaneous slices, and<br></span></li>
<li data-start="1782" data-end="1836"><span>comparing them to B’s own coordinate time intervals.<br></span></li></ul>
<span>So “according to B” = “as described in the coordinate system where B is at rest.”<br></span>
<span>This is <strong data-start="1929" data-end="1936">not</strong> an invariant statement — it depends on which frame you use.<br data-start="1996" data-end="1999">
Different inertial observers (A, B, N, etc.) disagree on which distant events are simultaneous.<br></span>
<hr data-start="2096" data-end="2099">
<h2 data-start="2101" data-end="2123">3️⃣ How they relate</h2>
<div class="_tableContainer_1rjym_1"><div tabindex="-1" class="group _tableWrapper_1rjym_13 flex w-fit flex-col-reverse"><table data-start="2125" data-end="2684" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="2125" data-end="2204"><tr data-start="2125" data-end="2204"><th data-start="2125" data-end="2134" data-col-size="sm">Phrase</th><th data-start="2134" data-end="2157" data-col-size="md">Mathematical meaning</th><th data-start="2157" data-end="2177" data-col-size="sm">Depends on frame?</th><th data-start="2177" data-end="2204" data-col-size="md">Physical interpretation</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="2224" data-end="2684"><tr data-start="2224" data-end="2355"><td data-start="2224" data-end="2248" data-col-size="sm">“Along B’s worldline”</td><td data-start="2248" data-end="2288" data-col-size="md">Proper time <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>τ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></td><td data-start="2288" data-end="2304" data-col-size="sm">❌ (invariant)</td><td data-start="2304" data-end="2355" data-col-size="md">B’s personal elapsed time (“in B’s experience”)</td></tr><tr data-start="2356" data-end="2493"><td data-start="2356" data-end="2375" data-col-size="sm">“According to B”</td><td data-start="2375" data-end="2433" data-col-size="md">Coordinate time differences defined by B’s simultaneity</td><td data-start="2433" data-end="2437" data-col-size="sm">✅</td><td data-start="2437" data-end="2493" data-col-size="md">How B <em data-start="2445" data-end="2456">describes</em> other clocks, e.g. “A’s runs slow”</td></tr><tr data-start="2494" data-end="2578"><td data-start="2494" data-end="2518" data-col-size="sm">“Along A’s worldline”</td><td data-start="2518" data-end="2545" data-col-size="md">Proper time <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>τ</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span></td><td data-start="2545" data-end="2549" data-col-size="sm">❌</td><td data-start="2549" data-end="2578" data-col-size="md">A’s personal elapsed time</td></tr><tr data-start="2579" data-end="2684"><td data-start="2579" data-end="2598" data-col-size="sm">“According to A”</td><td data-start="2598" data-end="2646" data-col-size="md">Coordinate-time description in A’s rest frame</td><td data-start="2646" data-end="2650" data-col-size="sm">✅</td><td data-start="2650" data-end="2684" data-col-size="md">How A <em data-start="2658" data-end="2669">describes</em> other clocks</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
<span>So:<br data-start="2689" data-end="2692">
✅ <strong data-start="2694" data-end="2742">“Along B’s worldline” ≈ “in B’s experience.”</strong><br data-start="2742" data-end="2745">
But ⚠️ it is <strong data-start="2758" data-end="2771">not quite</strong> the same as “according to B,” which usually means “in B’s frame.”<br></span>
<hr data-start="2839" data-end="2842">
<h2 data-start="2844" data-end="2875">4️⃣ Why Dingle stumbled here</h2>
<span>Dingle implicitly swapped these two meanings.<br></span>
<ul data-start="2924" data-end="3425"><li data-start="2924" data-end="3049"><span>In the first comparison (<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>), he uses the Lorentz factor relating <em data-start="3005" data-end="3026">A’s coordinate time</em> and <em data-start="3031" data-end="3048">B’s proper time</em>.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="3050" data-end="3185"><span>In the second (<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>), he switches which worldline provides the proper time — effectively using A’s frame as the reference.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="3186" data-end="3425"><span>He then compares the two as if they were symmetric statements “according to A” vs “according to B,” but they are not — they are <em data-start="3316" data-end="3347">different geometric intervals</em> in spacetime, not mere descriptions of the same events from two perspectives.<br></span></li></ul>
<span>Hence his apparent contradiction: <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>rate&nbsp;ratio</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> vs <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>γ</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>.<br data-start="3510" data-end="3513">
Both are correct, but they refer to <strong data-start="3549" data-end="3584">different segments of spacetime</strong>, not the same one viewed oppositely.<br></span>
<hr data-start="3623" data-end="3626">
<h2 data-start="3628" data-end="3647">5️⃣ The takeaway</h2>
<ul data-start="3649" data-end="3782"><li data-start="3649" data-end="3719"><span>“Along a worldline” → invariant, geometric, physical elapsed time.<br></span></li>
<li data-start="3720" data-end="3782"><span>“According to a frame” → coordinate, relative, conventional.<br></span></li></ul>
<span>So you can safely say:<br></span>
<blockquote data-start="3808" data-end="3964">
<span>“In B’s experience” is equivalent to “along B’s worldline.”<br data-start="3869" data-end="3872">
“According to B” is equivalent to “in B’s frame,” which involves simultaneity conventions.<br></span>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="3966" data-end="3969">
<span>Would you like me to draw a Minkowski diagram showing these worldlines and the two different “intervals” <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span></span>, so you can <em data-start="4114" data-end="4119">see</em> why Dingle’s two comparisons are geometrically different?<br></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></article><a href="data:application/octet-stream;base64," download="coverage.dat" style="color: blue; text-decoration: underline; cursor: pointer;">📎coverage.dat</a></div>
